The paper deals with the structural properties of graphs and their shortest paths, which are topics commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also makes use of homology, a topic in algebraic topology, which falls under the sub-category of geometric topology (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for new connections between shortest paths and topology, which could be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
